      "name": "Hemolysis index validation against in-vitro measurements",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5000 and 6000 RPM. Model underpredicts NIH by 18–31% across conditions. Stress-based hemolysis power law coefficients taken from literature without device-specific calibration.",
      "validationActivity": "Comparison of CFD-predicted NIH to in-vitro blood damage measurements under matched flow and speed conditions",
      "comparisonMetric": "Normalized index of hemolysis (g/100 L)",
      "comparisonResult": "CFD underpredicts NIH by 18–31% relative to in-vitro reference values"
    }
  ],
